<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,151,429]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,223,249]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Remarks.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[481,621,223,250]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 440" refId="ref72816" refString="Haig, J. (1960) The Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Anomura) of the Eastern Pacific. Allan Hancock Pacific Expedition, 24, 1 - 440." type="journal article" year="1960">Haig (1960)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haig" authorityYear="1957" box="[634,741,223,249]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Megalobrachium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="garthi">
<emphasis box="[634,741,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">M. garthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is superficially similar to another eastern Pacific species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lockington, 1878)" baseAuthorityName="Lockington" baseAuthorityYear="1878" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Megalobrachium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinuimanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">M. sinuimanus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lockington, W. N." box="[296,502,259,285]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="394 - 406" refId="ref74323" refString="Lockington, W. N. (1878) Remarks upon the Porcellanidea of the west coast of North America. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Serie 5, 2, 394 - 406. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222937808682444" type="journal article" year="1878">Lockington, 1878</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, especially in having a mesial lobe on the P1 carpus; in fact, they were recently confirmed to be sister species (Hiller &amp; Lessios 2019). However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haig" authorityYear="1957" box="[879,984,295,321]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Megalobrachium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="garthi">
<emphasis box="[879,984,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">M. garthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[999,1067,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1736,1760]" captionTargetBox="[308,1279,936,1712]" captionTargetId="figure-278@24.[308,1279,936,1712]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 7. Megalobrachium garthi Haig, 1957: extra-limital specimen, male (cl 3.4 mm, cw 3.1 mm) from Los Negritos off Bahía Málaga, Colombia (CRBM-UV-cr:2009-107), dorsal view [photograph by AA]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532201" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5532201/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
, showing a specimen from Bahía Málaga, 
<collectingCountry box="[252,364,331,358]" name="Colombia" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Colombia</collectingCountry>
) can be readily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lockington" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[777,945,331,356]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Megalobrachium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinuimanus">
